-- GM says July China auto sales up 11.1 percent year on year
-- 
-- Sun Aug 4, 2013 10:48pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/08/05/us-gm-china-sales-idUSBRE97402C20130805

 

 BEIJING  (Reuters) - General Motors Co ( GM.N ) and its Chinese joint ventures sold 221,580 vehicles in China in July, up 11.1 percent from a year earlier, the U.S. automaker said on Monday. 
 That compares with a 10.6 percent year-on-year gain in June. GM makes vehicles in China in partnership with FAW Group and SAIC Motor Corp Ltd ( 600104.SS ). (Reporting by  Jonathan Standing ; Editing by  Paul Tait )